                     <interp inst="t18270531-214-person1192" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. On the morning of the 11th I stopped the prisoner about two miles and a quarter from Northampton-row, with these tools in a basket; he said he was going to work at Saffron-hill, for one Colson - I said I knew him, and he had had no work for two years - I took him to the watch-house, and found Colson, who said he was not to work for him.</p>
